  <span id="freeText4516487401399256933" style="display:none">Perhaps this is the best way to state how much I loved this book, I just finished an ebook edition from my library and purchased a hard copy immediately for myself. There is just too much amazing information contained within to have it be an ebook. I have numerous digital highlights, but this is the sort of book that warrants writing in margins, notes, dog ears, and post-it tags, hence again why I have a copy in the mail. As a teacher of Ancient Civ there is so much fascinating content about Mesopotamia and Greece, as a feminist so many powerful but little known women (who knew Sargon the Great's daughter, Princess Enheduanna was the first recorded female writer!?!) are discussed, and as bibliophile there is so much to say about the power of written words. It is a must have on any bookshelf!</span>
