<div id="review_3973781251" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3973781251" />
    <a title="Pärvz Talibli" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/23201586-p-rvz-talibli"><img alt="Pärvz Talibli" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1625022821p2/23201586.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3973781251?book_show_action=true">May 19, 2021</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Pärvz Talibli" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Pärvz Talibli" href="/user/show/23201586-p-rvz-talibli">Pärvz Talibli</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3973781251" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer7508000474819902563">As expected, I really loved this book, which is probably Manguel&apos;s most comprehensive collection of essays on the history of the book and reading. Manguel just shines in chapters when he&apos;s looking into what roles the book and readers occupied in medieval cultures and while some of the chapters, such as the one on translation and authorship were not my favourites, overall the best part of this book was reading Manguel&apos;s passion and love for this project and his collection in every single chapter.</span>
  <span id="freeText7508000474819902563" style="display:none">As expected, I really loved this book, which is probably Manguel's most comprehensive collection of essays on the history of the book and reading. Manguel just shines in chapters when he's looking into what roles the book and readers occupied in medieval cultures and while some of the chapters, such as the one on translation and authorship were not my favourites, overall the best part of this book was reading Manguel's passion and love for this project and his collection in every single chapter. </span>
  <a data-text-id="7508000474819902563" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


